---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - MIDI Volume Control - Field Bureau + Werkstatt"
  description="Privacy Policy for MIDI Volume Control app"
  gradientOverlay="linear-gradient(to bottom, #4a4a4a, #2a2a2a)"
>
  <div class="relative min-h-screen flex flex-col">

    <!-- Breadcrumb Navigation -->
    <nav class="relative z-10 px-6 md:px-12 py-6">
      <div class="flex items-center space-x-2 text-sm text-white/80 drop-shadow-lg">
        <a href="/midi-volume" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">MIDI Volume Control</a>
        <span class="text-white/40">/</span>
        <span class="text-white">Privacy Policy</span>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <!-- Content -->
    <div class="relative z-10 px-6 md:px-12 py-12 flex-1">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">

        <!-- Header -->
        <div class="text-center mb-16 animate-fade-in-up" style="opacity: 0;">
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-light text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">
            Privacy Policy
          </h1>
          <p class="text-lg text-white/70 drop-shadow-lg">
            MIDI Volume Control
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 mt-4 drop-shadow-lg">
            Last updated: September 1, 2025
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Content Sections -->
        <div class="space-y-8 animate-fade-in-up" style="animation-delay: 200ms; opacity: 0;">

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">Overview</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-6 drop-shadow-lg">
              MIDI Volume Control ("the App") is designed with privacy in mind. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information when you use our macOS application for controlling system and Apple Music volume via MIDI controllers.
            </p>
            <div class="border border-white/30 rounded-xl p-6 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/10">
              <div class="flex items-start space-x-3">
                <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/>
                </svg>
                <div>
                  <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-white mb-2 drop-shadow-lg">Privacy-First Design</h3>
                  <p class="text-white/80 drop-shadow-lg">
                    <strong>We do not collect, store, or transmit any personal data.</strong> All processing happens locally on your Mac, and no information is sent to external servers.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">Information We Do Not Collect</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">
              MIDI Volume Control does not collect, store, or transmit:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white/80 leading-relaxed space-y-2 drop-shadow-lg">
              <li>Personal identification information</li>
              <li>Usage analytics or telemetry data</li>
              <li>MIDI controller data or configurations</li>
              <li>Volume settings or audio preferences</li>
              <li>System information or device identifiers</li>
              <li>Location data</li>
              <li>Network activity or browsing history</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">Local Data Processing</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-6 drop-shadow-lg">
              The App processes the following information locally on your device:
            </p>

            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="border border-white/20 rounded-xl p-6 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/5">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-white mb-3 drop-shadow-lg">MIDI Controller Data</h3>
                <p class="text-white/80 mb-2 drop-shadow-lg">
                  <strong>What:</strong> MIDI controller names, channel information, and CC mappings
                </p>
                <p class="text-white/80 mb-2 drop-shadow-lg">
                  <strong>Purpose:</strong> To identify and map your MIDI controllers for volume control
                </p>
                <p class="text-white/80 drop-shadow-lg">
                  <strong>Storage:</strong> Stored locally in macOS preferences, never transmitted
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="border border-white/20 rounded-xl p-6 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/5">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-white mb-3 drop-shadow-lg">App Settings</h3>
                <p class="text-white/80 mb-2 drop-shadow-lg">
                  <strong>What:</strong> Launch at login preference, Apple Music integration setting
                </p>
                <p class="text-white/80 mb-2 drop-shadow-lg">
                  <strong>Purpose:</strong> To remember your configuration between app launches
                </p>
                <p class="text-white/80 drop-shadow-lg">
                  <strong>Storage:</strong> Stored locally in macOS preferences
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">Permissions</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-6 drop-shadow-lg">
              The App may request the following system permissions:
            </p>

            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="flex items-start space-x-3 p-4 border border-white/20 rounded-xl backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/5">
                <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 19V6l12-3v13M9 19c0 1.105-1.343 2-3 2s-3-.895-3-2 1.343-2 3-2 3 .895 3 2zm12-3c0 1.105-1.343 2-3 2s-3-.895-3-2 1.343-2 3-2 3 .895 3 2zM9 10l12-3"/>
                </svg>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-medium text-white drop-shadow-lg">MIDI Access (Required)</h4>
                  <p class="text-white/80 text-sm drop-shadow-lg">
                    Allows the app to receive input from your MIDI controllers. This permission is essential for core functionality.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="flex items-start space-x-3 p-4 border border-white/20 rounded-xl backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/5">
                <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path d="M18.71 19.5C17.88 20.74 17 21.95 15.66 21.97C14.32 22 13.89 21.18 12.37 21.18C10.84 21.18 10.37 21.95 9.09997 22C7.78997 22.05 6.79997 20.68 5.95997 19.47C4.24997 17 2.93997 12.45 4.69997 9.39C5.56997 7.87 7.13997 6.91 8.85997 6.88C10.15 6.85 11.36 7.72 12.11 7.72C12.86 7.72 14.28 6.66 15.84 6.84C16.47 6.87 18.22 7.13 19.29 8.82C19.2 8.89 17.69 9.73 17.72 11.57C17.76 13.8 19.73 14.58 19.76 14.6C19.74 14.67 19.39 15.9 18.71 19.5ZM13 3.5C13.73 2.67 14.94 2.04 15.94 2C16.07 3.17 15.6 4.35 14.9 5.19C14.21 6.04 13.07 6.7 11.95 6.61C11.8 5.46 12.36 4.26 13 3.5Z"/>
                </svg>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-medium text-white drop-shadow-lg">Apple Music Automation (Optional)</h4>
                  <p class="text-white/80 text-sm drop-shadow-lg">
                    Only requested when you enable Apple Music volume control. Used exclusively for controlling Apple Music volume.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <p class="text-white/70 text-sm mt-4 drop-shadow-lg">
              You can revoke these permissions at any time through macOS System Settings → Privacy & Security.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">App Store Privacy</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">
              MIDI Volume Control is distributed through the Mac App Store and follows Apple's strict privacy guidelines:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white/80 leading-relaxed space-y-2 drop-shadow-lg">
              <li>The app runs in a secure sandbox environment</li>
              <li>All system access is controlled by macOS permissions</li>
              <li>No data is shared with third parties</li>
              <li>No advertising or tracking technologies are used</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">Data Security</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">
              Since all data processing happens locally on your Mac:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white/80 leading-relaxed space-y-2 drop-shadow-lg">
              <li>Your MIDI configurations are protected by macOS system security</li>
              <li>No data transmission means no risk of data breaches</li>
              <li>Settings are stored using secure macOS preferences system</li>
              <li>You maintain complete control over your data</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed drop-shadow-lg">
              Since we do not collect any personal information, the App is safe for users of all ages. No special provisions for children's data are needed as no data collection occurs.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">Changes to Privacy Policy</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed drop-shadow-lg">
              We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected in the "Last updated" date above. Continued use of the App after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">Contact Information</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed drop-shadow-lg">
              If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices, please contact us through the Mac App Store.
            </p>
          </section>

          <div class="border border-white/30 rounded-xl p-6 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/10">
            <div class="flex items-start space-x-3">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 15v2m-6 4h12a2 2 0 002-2v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2zm10-10V7a4 4 0 00-8 0v4h8z"/>
              </svg>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-white mb-2 drop-shadow-lg">Your Privacy Is Protected</h3>
                <p class="text-white/80 text-sm drop-shadow-lg">
                  MIDI Volume Control is designed to work entirely on your Mac without any data collection, tracking, or external communication. Your privacy and security are our top priorities.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Footer with black background -->
  <footer class="bg-black py-8 px-6 md:px-12">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-center text-white/30 text-xs tracking-wide">
        <span class="font-semibold">Field Bureau + Werkstatt</span>
        <span class="mx-2">•</span>
        © {new Date().getFullYear()} Field Bureau & Werkstatt LLC. All rights reserved.
      </p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>
